1. Anthropic Skills — skill-creator
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Source:   https://github.com/anthropics/skills
License:  Apache License 2.0
Copyright (c) Anthropic, PBC

The following files were absorbed (with modifications) from the upstream
`skills/skill-creator/scripts/` directory:

  - scripts/skill_eval/utils.py
      Original: scripts/utils.py
      Changes:  parse_skill_md() generalized to parse_md_frontmatter() to
                support both skill directories (containing SKILL.md) and
                single agent .md files. Added PyYAML dependency check with
                graceful degrade. Added path-name-based skill/agent inference.

  - scripts/skill_eval/quick_validate.py
      Original: scripts/quick_validate.py
      Changes:  Added --target={auto,skill,agent} flag for dual-mode
                validation. Added --format={text,json} output. Extended
                AGENT_ALLOWED frontmatter keyset for VAIS-specific fields
                (version, model, tools, memory, disallowedTools). Added
                progressive disclosure body-length checks (warn>500,
                fail>800). Restructured exit codes (0=pass / 1=warn /
                2=fail / 3=input-error).

The following files from the upstream skill-creator were intentionally
NOT absorbed (out of scope — see Plan v1.2 for rationale):

  - scripts/improve_description.py    (requires run_eval.py output)
  - scripts/run_eval.py               (Codex CLI subprocess loop)
  - scripts/run_loop.py               (iteration directory management)
  - scripts/aggregate_benchmark.py    (depends on run_eval/run_loop)
  - scripts/generate_report.py        (eval-viewer specific)
  - scripts/package_skill.py          (distribution tool)
  - eval-viewer/                      (local HTML server)
  - agents/{analyzer,comparator,grader}.md  (A/B comparison loop agents)
  - references/schemas.md             (above infrastructure schemas)

